  "prompt": "How can I add more topics here in Quora?",
  "response": "To add more topics on Quora, you can follow these steps:\n\n1. **Log In**: Ensure you are logged into your Quora account.\n\n2. **Search for Existing Topics**: Before creating a new topic, use the search bar to check if the topic already exists. \n\n3. **Create a Topic**:\n   - If the topic does not exist, click on the \u201cAdd Question\u201d button.\n   - You can type your question related to the new topic you want to create.\n   - When you start typing, look for the option to create a new topic. This usually appears if your question is not covered by existing topics.\n\n4. **Submit Your Idea**: Follow the prompts to submit your new topic.\n\n5. **Topic Approval**: Your suggested topic may require approval from Quora\u2019s moderation team before it goes live.\n\n6. **Contribute to Existing Topics**: Once your topic is added, consider contributing by asking questions, answering, and engaging with others in that space.\n\nRemember that Quora guidelines and policies should be followed to ensure that the topics are relevant and appropriate.",
